   (a) create a plot of the pdf with appropriate axis labels, and a title.

   (b) create a plot of the CDF with appropriate axis labels, and a title.

   (c) compute P(X $\le$ 17.2).

   (d) compute P(15 $\le$ X $\le$ 20).

4. Let X1 ~ Gamma(shape=3.5, rate=2) and X2 ~ Gamma(shape=4, rate=1.2)¶

   (a) plot the pdfs of X1 and X2 on the same plot in different colors with a legend.

   (b) plot the CDFs of X1 and X2 on the same plot in different colors with a legend.

   (c) Determine the median of each distribution

   (d) Determine P(2 < X < 10) for each distribution

In [136]:
# 4.(a)
curve(dgamma(x, 3.5, 2), from=0, to=11, col="red", ylab = "density",
      main = "pdfs of Gamma(3.5, 2) and Gamma(4, 1.2)")
curve(dgamma(x, 4, 1.2), add=T)
abline(0,0)
legend(6, 0.45, legend=c("Gamma(3.5, 2)","Gamma(4, 1.2)"),lty=c(1,1),col=c("red","black"))
In [138]:
# 4.(b)
curve(pgamma(x, 3.5, 2), from=0, to=11, col="red", ylab = "density",
      main = "CDFs of Gamma(3.5, 2) and Gamma(4, 1.2)")
curve(pgamma(x, 4, 1.2), add=T)
abline(0,0)
legend(6, 0.6, legend=c("Gamma(3.5, 2)","Gamma(4, 1.2)"),lty=c(1,1),col=c("red","black"))
In [139]:
# 4.(c)
qgamma(0.5, 3.5, 2)  # median of gamma(3.5, 2)
qgamma(0.5, 4, 1.2)  # median of gamma(4, 1.2)
1.58645279888038
3.06005062404241
In [135]:
# 4.(d)
pgamma(10, 3.5, 2) - pgamma(2, 3.5, 2)  # P(2 < X < 10) of gamma(3.5, 2)
pgamma(10, 4, 1.2) - pgamma(2, 4, 1.2)  # P(2 < X < 10) of gamma(4, 1.2)
0.332592643808921
0.776431119828526

5. Let X1 ~ LNorm(mu=2, sigma=1.5) and X2 ~ Gamma(shape=3.5, rate=0.7)¶

   (a) plot the pdfs of X1 and X2 on the same plot in different colors with a legend.

   (b) Add the means to the x-axis of the plot in part (a). Use text label the means.

   (c) plot the CDFs of X1 and X2 on the same plot in different colors with a legend.

   (d) Add a horizontal line at height y = 0.5 to the CDF plot. Where the line intersects the curve is the median of the distribution.

In [178]:
# 5.(a)
curve(dlnorm(x, 2, 1.5), from=0, to=30, col="red", ylab = "density", ylim = c(0, 0.2),
      main = "pdfs of LNorm(2, 1.5) and Gamma(3.5, 0.7)")
curve(dgamma(x, 3.5, 0.7), col = "blue", add=T)
abline(0,0)
legend(10, 0.17, legend=c("LNorm(2, 1.5)","Gamma(3.5, 0.7)"),lty=c(1,1),col=c("red","blue"))

# 5.(b)
mean_lnorm = exp(2+((1.5)^2)/2)
mean_gamma = 3.5/0.7
points(mean_lnorm, 0, col="red", pch=19)
text(mean_lnorm, 0.02, "Mean of LNorm", col= "red")
points(mean_gamma, 0, col="blue", pch=19)
text(mean_gamma, 0.02, "Mean of Gamma", col= "blue")
In [199]:
# 5.(c)
curve(plnorm(x, 2, 1.5), from=0, to=50, col="red", ylab = "density", ylim = c(0,1),
      main = "CDFs of LNorm(2, 1.5) and Gamma(3.5, 0.7)")
curve(pgamma(x, 3.5, 0.7), col = "blue", add=T)
abline(0,0)
legend(30, 0.7, legend=c("LNorm(2, 1.5)","Gamma(3.5, 0.7)"),lty=c(1,1),col=c("red","blue"))

# 5.(d)
abline(h=0.5)
text(11, 0.52, "median")
